I just think it ruins the pacing and immersion of chapter 8. you can get so overleveld doing this trial cuz not only do the enemies give a ton of points, but you have to go through it twice to get your reward. I mean.... how are you supposed to get hype for this chapter when you can defeat bosses in mere seconds. It just feels like an extra challenge that you #8217;re supposed to do post-game. A lot of games keep their hardest task after the main game is beaten. I think flopside 100 trials should #8217;ve been post game only like the duel of 100. And yes, the Duel of 100 being post game makes sense. cuz you save it at the end of the main campaign. But we all know the duel of 100 is the easiest of them all ( even though its the second most time consuming). Usually at chapter 8, you #8217;re level 15, 16, or 17. But if you do flopside 100 trials first, you can be level 30+ doin way more damage than intended. This can make the last few bosses a joke. Especially Count Bleck and Super dimentio because you can use bowser to do twice the amount of ridiculous damage you already do. Idk, its just my opinion.
I think Bonechill should #8217;ve atleast pushed you away after you super jumped him. Why doesn #8217;t he use his #8220;talons #8221; to push you away.
